#: 49920
msgid ""
"This man looks like a bitter, cantankerous old codger. His mouth is twisted "
"into frown that becomes even more severe as he notices you coming his way. "
"\"Merriman my name may be, but merry I am not! Off with you, young one! No "
"time for the likes of you!\" He goes into a fit of coughing from the "
"exertion of shooing you away so loudly."
msgstr ""

#: 49921 49924
msgid "\"Wait... Dolora wanted me to speak with you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49922 49925
msgid "\"Fine... farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49923
msgid "Merriman gives you a sour, withering look. \"Go away,\" he hisses."
msgstr ""

#: 49926
msgid ""
"Merriman eyes you suspiciously. \"That so? About *what,* eh? Hmm? Well?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49927
msgid ""
"\"She says that you're her first love, and that so long as you hold the keys "
"to her heart, she'll never be free to love another.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49928
msgid "\"Forget it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49929
msgid ""
"\"She told you that, eh? I'm surprised. Perhaps leaving her in under "
"Mistress Grace's tutelage did what I couldn't... started to develop her "
"*feelings.* In any case...\" He pats a pocket on his tunic. \"...I won't "
"just *give* the keys to you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49930
msgid "\"Wait - those are literally 'the keys to her heart?'\""
msgstr ""

#: 49931
msgid "\"What do you want for them, then?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49932
msgid "\"Then perhaps I'll just *take* them from you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49933
msgid "\"We'll talk about them later. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49934
msgid ""
"\"The only way you'll be *taking* my keys, young one, is by prying them from "
"my cold, dead fingers! And I'm uncertain of the wisdom in starting a row in "
"the Civic Festhall...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49935
msgid "Attack him."
msgstr ""

#: 49936
msgid "\"Granted. So - are these literally 'the keys to her heart?'\""
msgstr ""

#: 49937
msgid "\"All right. What did you want for them, Merriman?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49938
msgid "\"In that case, farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49939
msgid ""
"He nods. \"That they are. Dolora's a Construct; didn't you know that? A "
"creature of sorcery and clockwork mechanics she is, and one of my finest "
"creations.\" Merriman sighs. \"But cold, without emotion or character. I "
"brought her to the Brothel and 'set' her so that she could not leave, in the "
"hopes that the constant contact with so many others would begin develop her "
"own personality. The keys are the tools used to 'set' her; she wants them "
"because she feels that they're limiting her personal growth now, I suspect.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49940
msgid "\"Then why don't you just return them to her?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49941
msgid "\"What do you want for the keys?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49942
msgid "\"Perhaps I'll just *take* the keys from you...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49943
msgid "\"That's all I wished to know. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49944
msgid ""
"Merriman scowls. \"Because I've become a cruel and bitter old man, who sees "
"he can get something out of you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49945
msgid "\"Go on, then... what do you want?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49946
msgid "\"Not if I just take the keys, Merriman...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49947
msgid "\"We'll discuss this later. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49948
msgid ""
"\"I want... I want to forget. I've lived almost one hundred and fifty years, "
"now, and I've seen every sensory stone I've cared to in this grand hall. "
"I've little time left to live, and am too weak to go out in search of wholly "
"new experiences... so I need to find a way to forget them all. That way, I "
"can start again in my final days...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49949
msgid "\"So... do I just wallop you in the back of the head, or what?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49950
msgid "\"How can I help?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49951
msgid "\"I'll think about it. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49952
msgid ""
"Merriman wanted me to help him lose his memories before he gave me the keys "
"to Dolora's heart. I suppose I'll have to look for something that'd do that "
"to a person, then bring it back to him... Merriman himself suggested water "
"from the River Styx as one possibility."
msgstr ""

#: 49953
msgid "\"No, you bloodthirsty lummox!\""
msgstr ""

#: 49954
msgid ""
"\"I'll need something... some item, some concoction... that will allow me to "
"forget. Like a draught of the river Styx; something like that.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49955 49958
msgid ""
"\"Here, take this mug... it holds a Dark Bird of Ocanthus, a sliver of ice "
"from the River Styx. It should wipe your memories clean...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49956
msgid "\"Right. I'll return if I find something... farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49957
msgid ""
"Merriman squints up at you. \"Well? Have you something that will wipe my "
"mind of these accursed memories? I certainly hope you haven't returned "
"without... you'll never get the keys to Dolora's heart, that way.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49959
msgid "\"Perhaps I'll just take the keys, Merriman...\""
msgstr ""

#: 49960
msgid "\"No, I don't. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49961
msgid ""
"Merriman takes the mug and removed a piece of paper from his pocket. He "
"tilts the mug back and takes the ice into his mouth... it melts instantly, "
"leaving him with a somewhat startled expression..."
msgstr ""

#: 49962 49963
msgid "\"Merriman...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 49964
msgid ""
"Merriman looks at you, confused, then at the paper in his hands. He reads "
"aloud: \"Congratulations, Merriman: you've begun again. Thank the man in "
"front of you and give him they key in your pocket. Speak to Splinter, the "
"man at the door to this building, for more information.\" He looks to you "
"again. \"Well... it would seem I owe you thanks, good sir. Here... take this "
"key. I'd best find this 'Splinter' fellow and find out what's going on!\""
msgstr ""

#: 49965
msgid "\"Thanks, Merriman. Good luck.\""
msgstr ""

#: 49966
msgid ""
"Merriman looks at you, confused, then at the paper in his hands. He reads "
"aloud: \"Congratulations, Merriman: you've begun again. Thank the man in "
"front of you and give him they key in your pocket. Speak to Splinter, the "
"man at the door to this building, for more information.\" He looks to you "
"again. \"Well... it would seem I owe you thanks, good sir. Hmm... I don't "
"seem to have a key on me, though. Perhaps someone took it from me. So sorry! "
"Well, I'd best find this 'Splinter' fellow and find out what's going on!\""
msgstr ""

#: 49967
msgid "\"Good luck, Merriman. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66580
msgid ""
"I brought back a piece of frozen Styxx-ice -- a Dark Bird of Ocanthus -- to "
"Merriman. Upon consuming it, he lost all his memories. It's what he wanted, "
"though I can't say I envy the fellow."
msgstr ""
